@node Install "Installation"
Installation
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   This part is very easy.

   All you have to do is to extract the archive to anywhere you wish
   (preferable to a HD). But an ordinary floppy would do as well...

   Then you just have to run the executable or why not just make it simple and
   click the icon... ;)

@endnode

@node Desc "Description"
Description
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   What is this then???

   This is yet another MandelBrot generator with some quite nice features (which I will
   explain in the usage part of this text.. :)

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"
Usage
¯¯¯¯¯
   The program has a pretty selfexplaining GUI, but there are some things I would
   like to say about it!

   1) The "Zoom" option. The lower value, the more the program zooms into
      the mandelbrot / render

   2) The "Jump no lines" determines how many lines which will be skipped when you
      push the right mouse button.

   3) The "Colours" cycle bar sets the number of colours in the rendered image, but it
      also sets the number of interations / pixel. ie. Less colours -> faster render but
      with lower detail!

   4) You MUST choose a place to zoom on the render screen before you can use the GUI after
      a render...

      Well.. I guess that's about it! HAVE FUN!

@endnode
@node Req "Requirements"
Requirements
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   This produkt requires an AMIGA equipped with the AGA chipset and OS 3.0 at least.
   It does NOT need an FPU as many other Mandelbrot generators. (And that's one of
   the main reasons why I made this program in the first place :) )


@endnode

